'''Daniel Minahan''' is an American director. He has worked on the HBO series ''[[wikipedia:True Blood|True Blood]]'', ''[[wikipedia:John From Cincinnati|John From Cincinnati]]'', ''[[wikipedia:Deadwood (TV series)|Deadwood]]'' and ''[[wikipedia:Six Feet Under (TV series)|Six Feet Under]]'', as well as ''[[wikipedia:Grey's Anatomy|Grey's Anatomy]]'' and ''[[wikipedia:The L Word|The L Word]]''.

For ''[[Game of Thrones]]'' Minahan directed episodes 6, 7 and 8 of the [[Season 1|first season]]. He returned for the [[Season 3|third season]] and helmed the season premiere &quot;[[Valar Dohaeris]]&quot; and the second episode &quot;[[Dark Wings, Dark Words]].&quot;&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Season_3_Directors/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;

